Merton H. Miller (1990), 
George J. Stigler (1982), 
Gary Becker (1992), 
Robert E. Lucas Jr. (1995), 
Robert W. Fogel (1993), 
Eugene F. Fama (2013), 
Roger B. Myerson (2007), 
Ronald H. Coase (1991), 
Milton Friedman (1976), 
Richard H. Thaler (2017), 
Theodore W. Schultz (1979), 
Douglas Diamond (2022), 
Lars Peter Hansen (2013), and 
James J. Heckman (2000).
results.cypher: MATCH (s:Scholar)-[:WON]->(p:Prize) WHERE toLower(p.category) CONTAINS 'economics' MATCH (s)-[:AFFILIATED_WITH]->(i:Institution) WHERE toLower(i.name) CONTAINS 'university of chicago' RETURN DISTINCT s.knownName, p.awardYear, i.name AS Institution

results.question: Which scholars won Physiology or Medicine in 1920?
results.answer: The scholar who won Physiology or Medicine in 1920 is August Krogh.
results.cypher: MATCH (s:Scholar)-[:WON]->(p:Prize) WHERE toLower(p.category) CONTAINS 'medicine' AND p.awardYear = 1920 RETURN DISTINCT s.knownName

results.question: Which scholars affiliated with CERN won a prize in Physics?

results.question: Which scholars affiliated with University of Oxford won a prize in Chemistry?
results.answer: The scholars affiliated with the University of Oxford who won a prize in Chemistry are Sir Robert Robinson in 1947, Sir Cyril Hinshelwood in 1956, Dorothy Crowfoot Hodgkin in 1964, and Frederick Soddy in 1921.

results.question: Which scholars born in Switzerland won the Physics prize between 1980 and 2020?
results.answer: The scholars born in Switzerland who won the Physics prize between 1980 and 2020 are K. Alex Müller in 1987, and Didier Queloz and Michel Mayor in 2019.
results.cypher: MATCH (s:Scholar)-[:BORN_IN]->(:City)-[:IS_CITY_IN]->(:Country {name: 'Switzerland'}), (s)-[:WON]->(p:Prize) WHERE toLower(p.category) CONTAINS 'physics' AND p.awardYear >= 1980 AND p.awardYear <= 2020 RETURN s.knownName AS scholar, p.awardYear AS award_year ORDER BY p.awardYear

results.question: How many female scholars won a Nobel Prize between 1980 and 2000?
results.answer: Between 1980 and 2000, 4 female scholars won a Nobel Prize.
results.cypher: MATCH (s:Scholar)-[:WON]->(p:Prize) WHERE toLower(s.gender) = 'female' AND p.awardYear >= 1980 AND p.awardYear <= 2000 RETURN count(s) as female_scholars

results.question: Which scholars have won more than one Nobel Prize?
results.answer: The scholars who have won more than one Nobel Prize are Frederick Sanger, John Bardeen, Linus Pauling, Marie Curie, and K. Barry Sharpless.
results.cypher: MATCH (s:Scholar)-[:WON]->(p:Prize) WITH s, count(p) AS prize_count WHERE prize_count > 1 RETURN s.knownName

results.question: How many Physics laureates were born in Paris?
results.answer: There are 3 Physics laureates born in Paris.
results.cypher: MATCH (s:Scholar)-[:WON]->(p:Prize) WHERE toLower(p.category) = 'physics' MATCH (s)-[:BORN_IN]->(c:City) WHERE toLower(c.name) CONTAINS 'paris' RETURN count(s) as physics_laureates

results.question: How many scholars won a prize with a 1/3 share portion?
results.answer: There are 222 scholars who won a prize with a 1/3 share portion.
results.cypher: MATCH (s:Scholar)-[r:WON]->(p:Prize) WHERE toLower(r.portion) = '1/3' RETURN count(s) as count
